Interface ActionExecutor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        void execute(Environment env,
           boolean dispatch,
           Action action,
           java.lang.Object... parameters)
        Schedules to execute an action and waits for it to finish.
        Parameters:
        env - Environment.
        dispatch - if true the action is executed on UI system dispatch thread. This is usually necessary to invoke methods of the UI to get the correct state or to update it.
        action - Action to execute.
        parameters - Parameters to pass to action.run() method.

      • executeDetached

        void executeDetached(Environment env,
                   boolean dispatch,
                   Action action,
                   java.lang.Object... parameters)
        Schedules to execute an action and exits immediately. Used to be called DoSomethingNoBlock operations in jemmy2.
        Parameters:
        env - Environment.
        dispatch - if true the action is executed on UI system dispatch thread. This is usually necessary to invoke methods of the UI to get the correct state or to update it.
        action - Action to execute.
        parameters - Parameters to pass to action.run() method.

      • isInAction

        boolean isInAction()
        Checks whether the current thread is already performing an action.
        Returns:
        true if the current thread is already performing an action.
        See Also:
        AbstractExecutor#isDispatchThread()

      • waitQuiet

        void waitQuiet(Timeout waitTime)
        Waits for no activities to be going on. Implementation may be different for different mechanisms.
        Parameters:
        waitTime - maximum time for waiting.
        See Also:
        AbstractExecutor.isQuiet()
